hh3cVoiceInterface.name: hh3cVoiceInterface

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

hh3cVoiceInterface.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.hh3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cVoiceInterface.description: This MIB file is to provide the definition of the voice interface general configuration.

hh3cVoiceIfConfigTable.name: hh3cVoiceIfConfigTable
hh3cVoiceIfConfigTable.description: The table contains configurable parameters for both analog voice interface and digital voice interface.

hh3cVoiceIfConfigEntry.name: hh3cVoiceIfConfigEntry
hh3cVoiceIfConfigEntry.description: The entry of voice interface table.

hh3cVoiceIfCfgCngOn.name: hh3cVoiceIfCfgCngOn
hh3cVoiceIfCfgCngOn.description: This object indicates whether the silence gaps should be filled with background noise. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line.

hh3cVoiceIfCfgNonLinearSwitch.name: hh3cVoiceIfCfgNonLinearSwitch
hh3cVoiceIfCfgNonLinearSwitch.description: This object expresses the nonlinear processing is enable or disable for the voice interface. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line. Currently, only digital voice subscriber lines can be set disabled.

hh3cVoiceIfCfgInputGain.name: hh3cVoiceIfCfgInputGain
hh3cVoiceIfCfgInputGain.description: This object indicates the amount of gain added to the receiver side of the voice interface. Unit is 0.1 db. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line.

hh3cVoiceIfCfgOutputGain.name: hh3cVoiceIfCfgOutputGain
hh3cVoiceIfCfgOutputGain.description: This object indicates the amount of gain added to the send side of the voice interface. Unit is 0.1 db. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line.

hh3cVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch.name: hh3cVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch
hh3cVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch.description: This object indicates whether the echo cancellation is enabled. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line.

hh3cVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelDelay.name: hh3cVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelDelay
hh3cVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelDelay.description: This object indicates the delay of the echo cancellation for the voice interface. This value couldn't be modified unless hh3cVoiceIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch is enable. Unit is milliseconds. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line. The default value of this object is 32.

hh3cVoiceIfCfgTimerDialInterval.name: hh3cVoiceIfCfgTimerDialInterval
hh3cVoiceIfCfgTimerDialInterval.description: The interval, in seconds, between two dialing numbers. The default value of this object is 10 seconds. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 with loop-start or ground-start protocol voice subscriber line.

hh3cVoiceIfCfgTimerFirstDial.name: hh3cVoiceIfCfgTimerFirstDial
hh3cVoiceIfCfgTimerFirstDial.description: The period of time, in seconds, before dialing the first number. The default value of this object is 10 seconds. It is applicable to FXO, FXS subscriber lines and E1/T1 with loop-start or ground-start protocol voice subscriber line.

hh3cVoiceIfCfgPrivateline.name: hh3cVoiceIfCfgPrivateline
hh3cVoiceIfCfgPrivateline.description: This object indicates the E.164 phone number for plar mode. It is applicable to FXO, FXS, E&M subscriber lines and E1/T1 voice subscriber line.

hh3cVoiceIfCfgRegTone.name: hh3cVoiceIfCfgRegTone
hh3cVoiceIfCfgRegTone.description: This object uses 2 or 3 letter country code specify voice parameters of different countrys. This value will take effect on all voice interfaces of all cards on the device.
